Zimbabwe Public Service Minister, Tsvangirai Adviser, Dies, Radio VOP Says

-- B y   B r i a n   L a t h a m
-- 
2011-08-05T09:57:06Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-05/zimbabwe-public-service-minister-tsvangirai-adviser-dies-radio-vop-says.html
Zimbabwe’s public service minister,
Eliphas Mukonoweshuro, died in  South Africa ,  Radio Voice of the
People  reported, citing Movement for Democratic Change spokesman
Douglas Mwonzora.  Mukonoweshuro was an adviser to  Morgan Tsvangirai , the
southern African nation’s prime minister and leader of the MDC,
and proved last year that 70,000 non-existent state workers were
on the government’s payroll, the Harare-based broadcaster
reported on its website, without giving details of his death.  He had traveled to South Africa for treatment after feeling
unwell, it said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Brian Latham in Johannesburg at 
 blatham@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Antony Sguazzin at 
 asguazzin@bloomberg.net  